{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Calibri;}{\f1 Courier New;}}\paperw11907\paperh16840\margl1440\margr1440\margt1080\margb1080\fs22 BMI Health Checker\line \line Assignment Information\line Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology\line Civil Engineering Department\line Module: Programming Fundamentals for Technicians (GST 05117)\line Class: OD24CE-2 | Assignment Type: Group | Assignment No: 3\line Group Number: 11 | Submission Date: March 1, 2026\line \line Group Members\line 1. ABDULAZIZ MAHYORO (240121429579)\line 2. LAWRENCE MMATAMBWE (220121417491)\line 3. ELIAH HANGO (240121476067)\line 4. HUSSEIN OMARY (240121449049)\line 5. ROBERT JAMES (240121479897)\line 6. GIDEON OLANG'U (240121429421)\line 7. MOSES MFUSE (24012317533)\line 8. GLORIA DAUDI (240121453512)\line \line Brief Explanation (One-Page Summary)\line We developed this project as a simple but useful console program to strengthen our understanding of programming fundamentals. This project is designed to receive user values, process them with conditions and calculations, then display final output.\line In this project (BMI Health Checker), c console program that records bmi entries, classifies categories, and prints statistics.\line \line How the Program Works\line 1. It shows a clear prompt/menu to the user.\line 2. It accepts and validates user input to avoid wrong values.\line 3. It processes data using conditions, loops, and calculations.\line 4. It prints final results in a readable format.\line \line Concepts Practiced\line - Variables and data types\line - Arithmetic operators\line - Conditionals\line - Arrays and structs\line - Functions\line - Menu-driven flow\line \line Sample Output (short example)\line === BMI Health Checker ===\line 1. Add BMI Record\line 2. View All Records\line 3. View BMI Statistics\line 4. Exit\line Choose an option: 1\line Enter name: Sam\line Enter weight in kg: 70\line \line Presentation Note\line This mini project is intentionally simple, focused, and easy to explain during presentation.}